The subject covered in this report, is automatic order of goods for supermarkets. The problems are based on the rise of wasted food in Denmark, and how to solve this problem. The aim is to create a more efficient way to automatically decide, how much goods should be ordered based on parameters such a prior sale and current stock. The goal is to develop a software library, with these capabilities build in. In extension to the software library, an application will be developed, such that the capabilities of the software library can be presented. The application will be based on a graphical user interface, developed to be user friendly, easy to navigate and use. The report explains the process of developing the software library and the application, and the thoughts behind the design of the combined system.
